						               													<description>Each player should have three 12oz beverages in front of them (alcoholic or nonalcoholic). The game involves rules that can either add sips or remove sips from a player's glass&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn players will roll the die and move their bottle cap piece to the corresponding square. There are 36 squares in the game. The squares may have you draw a card, play a mini-game, or require action. Each square will either decrease the number of drinks in your glass or increase your lifespan, so to speak. (I.e. giving drinks increases your glasses capacity while taking drinks lowers it)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Be among the first three players to make it to the finish line without finishing your three drinks. The game is a race to the finish with a gold medal (1st). silver (2nd), and bronze (3rd).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After a player gets sent back to the start or finishes their three drinks and is forced back to the start, they are not required to follow the &amp;ldquo;lifeline&amp;rdquo; rule but must follow the drinking rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when three players have reached the finish, achieving gold, silver, and bronze. Once a player has reached the finish, they are exempt from mini-games or drinking aspects of the game (unless they choose to join the fun).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
